BAB BASE-ATTACK-BONUS
@c-----------------------------------------------------------------@n

Melee no longer uses the classic D&D THAC0 system. Now,
base armor class is 10, and characters gain (based on class)
a base attack bonus (BAB).  For instance, a 5th level mobile
might have 15 armor class and a 5th level fighter might have a
BAB of 5. We still use a 20 sided dice. So if one rolls a 9,
the formula will give: BAB 5 + Dice 9 < 15 Armor Class. That
will result in a miss, 14 < 15. At this stage the info
is displayed to the attacker to see how they are doing.


Base attack bonus (BAB) is a simple system that determines
how effective you are at conquering an opponents armor class.
BAB + 1d20 is compared to your opponent's armor class to see
whether you hit or not.

The current formulas for the classes are as follow:


Class                BAB

Wizard          Level / 2
Rogue           Level * 3 / 4
Warrior         Level
Cleric          Level * 3 / 4
Monk            Level * 3 / 4

See also:  ARMOR-CLASS CRITICAL-HIT
For more recent info on ARMOR-CLASS, please see:  ARMOR-RATING
