BUILDING-RULES
@n
By Ambanya
@n
Rooms:
@n
    -Rooms may not be repeated without special exception. This includes
roads. It excludes mazes.
@n
Room Titles:
@n
    -Titles must not be repeated ad nauseum, unless it's a maze.
Differentiate each one, even for roads and similar rooms, where possible.
    -Every word in a room title must be capitalized, excepting only
determiners and prepositions, which may or may not be as befits your
preference. The first word must always be capitalized. Example: "A Long,
Dark, Road through the Marsh" may also be "A Long, Dark Road Through The
Marsh".
    -Titles should contain adjectives. Remember that most players will
only see the title in a room. Use description words wherever possible.
    -Titles may not contain the word "you." They may not contain actions
or reactions taken by the player.
@n    
Room Description:
@n
    -All rdescs must be formatted with /fi.
    -All rdescs must be longer than two lines. Two lines and a word on
the third is acceptible. The ideal rdesc is 5 or 6 lines, so aim for that.
    -All rdescs must contain at least one adjective.
    -Rdescs may not contain the word "you." They may not contain actions
or reactions taken by the player.
    -Outdoor rdescs should usually not mention weather, sounds that are
time-dependent (like things awake during the day), and other things that
are not constant for everyone standing in that spot. Exceptions are made
for quest-important rooms.
    -Rdescs may mention fuction of things that aren't immediately apparent
where important for setting. Builders are not limited to laundry lists of
physical objects; rather, they should use rdescs to establish setting.
@n    
Room Exits:
@n
    -The exits for NESW must have descriptions in every room. No exceptions.
    -Exit descriptions for U and D are optional, but generally recommended
where reasonable.
    -Exit descriptions may not be longer than a single line.
    -Exit descriptions should only mention activity, sounds, etc in adjacent
rooms in vague terms. Exceptions are made for quest-important rooms.
@n    
Extra descs:
@n
    -Every noun in a title, rdesc, exitdesc, or extra desc, should probably
have its own extra desc. This is not a rule, but a strong suggestion.
    -Every noun from the above rule that is particularly noticeable or
important must have an extra desc.
    -Extra descs may use "you", contain actions or reactions made by the
player, break immersion with humor, etc. The purpose is still description,
though, so be reasonable.
    -Don't be stingy with extra descs. Yes, that's a rule. Ambanya decides
if you've broken it.
@N
Mobs:
@N
   -Mobs should have at least one adjective in the name. No "a fly". It's
"an annoying, buzzing fly." The ONLY exception is named mobs.
   -mdescs may not contain the word "you" or contain actions made by the
player. General feelings are okay, like the line "A sense of dread follows
wherever the Darklord Kraal goes."
@n
