CLAN CLANS

Usage: clan

The clan command simply gives a list of clan-based commands that are avilable 
to you.

If you wish to apply to join a clan, you should look at the available choices
by typing @yclan info@n to see a list of clans, then @yclan info <num>@n to see more
information about a particular clan.

When you have found the clan you like, type @yclan apply <num>@n to apply to that
clan.  You will receive a message when your application has been approved.

See Also: CLAN-INFO CLAN-APPLY

#0
CLAN-APPLY CLAN-APPLICATIONS

Usage: clan apply <clan ID>

The clan apply command is used to apply to join a clan.  You can apply to only
one clan at a time.  If you apply to a different clan, then your previous
application is cancelled.

After you have applied, the clan leader of clan admins must approve your 
application.  You will receive a message when this happens.  Your application
can only be approved while you are online.

See Also: CLAN

#0
CLAN-AWARD AWARDING-CLANPOINTS

Usage: clan award <member name> <num>

Usually reserved for clan leaders, this command allows you to award clan points
to deserving clan members.

See Also: CLAN

#0
CLAN-BALANCE

Usage: clan balance

Shows the clan's current bank balance.

See Also: CLAN-DEPOSIT CLAN-WITHDRAW

#0
CLAN-CLAIM CLAIMING-ZONES CLAIMING-AREAS

Usage: clan claim

To claim a zone, there are certain pre-requisites that you must perform.

* You clan's popularity in the zone must meet the minimum requirement.

* You must be standing in the zone you wish to claim.

Once a zone has been claimed by your clan, all members of other clans must pay
a tax on money gained from kills within that zone.  This tax is paid directly
into the clan bank, where the clan leader can spend it as they choose, such as
sharing it between their own clan members, buying a clanhall or clan eq.

See Also: CLAN POPULARITY

#0
CLAN-CREATE

Usage: clan create <plr> <name>

Creates a new clan, with <plr> as the leader.
The clan name may be up to 60 characters long, and include color codes and
spaces.  If the name exceeds 60 characters, it will be truncated.

See Also: CLAN-DESTROY CLANSET

#31
CLAN-DEMOTE CLAN-DEMOTION

Usage: clan demote

This command is used to lower a clan member's rank by 1.

You must have access to this command, and be of a higher rank than the person
that you wish to demote.

See Also: CLAN CLAN-PROMOTE

#0
CLAN-DEPOSIT CLAN-BANK

Usage: clan deposit <amount>

Allows your hard-earned money to be donated to your clan's funds.  The clan bank
account should steadily increase as your clan claims zones, but you may have a
little excess gold to get rid of, and wish to donate it towards a clanhall or
clan eq.

Most clan members are usually able to deposit into the clan bank, but often only
clan admin and the clan leader can withdraw it.

See Also: CLAN-WITHDRAW CLAN-CLAIM

#0
CLAN-DESTROY

Usage: clan destroy <clan>

Permanently remove a clan from the MUD.  All members of the clan will be
expelled from the clan.  If they are online, they will get a message informing 
them that the clan has been disbanded.

See Also: CLAN-CREATE CLAN-UNCLAIM CLANSET

#31
CLAN-EDIT CLAN-OLC

Usage: clan edit

Clan leaders may use the clan edit command to enter a menu-based editor (OLC),
that allows several options to be changed, including all clan priveleges and 
ranks.

Imps can also use the clan editor, by specifying a clan ID number on the end of
the command.

See Also: CLAN

