CRAFTING

The crafting system on Luminari is heavily influenced by d20MUD's system,
it was re-written by Zusuk for TBA codebase and adapted to Luminari's
game mechanics.

There are 3 primary elements to the crafting system:
Creation
Modification
Auto-Crafting Quest

Creation is done with the CREATE command.  In order to make an item, you
need a MOLD, materials, optionally an enchantment crystal and money.
You'll need to take these items and put them inside a CRAFTING-KIT and
use the CREATE command to make the item.

Modification includes:  AUGMENT, CONVERT, RESTRING and RESIZE.  These
crafting commands require you put the item you want to modify in the
crafting kit to be used.  Refer to the respective help files for more
details.

Auto-Crafting Quest represents local militias need for weapons, armor
and other war supplies to supplement their battle against the growing
monster presence in the world.  Refer to the SUPPLYORDER help file for
more info.

See Also:  AUGMENT CONVERT RESTRING SUPPLYORDER RESIZE CRAFTCHECK
            CREATE CRAFTING-KIT AUTOCRAFT DISENCHANT

