#31
MULTICLASS MULTICLASSING

Multi-classing is the ability to select how you advance your training.

There are different systems of "multi-classing."  The system we are NOT
using is advancing completely in one class, then adding another class
on top of it.

Our system of multi-classing means that you are sacrificing advancement
in one class in the preference of the diversity offered by advancing in
another class.

Example:  You started as a 1st level Warrior and have gained enough
experience to advance to the 2nd level.  You can choose to continue your
advancement as a Warrior, thus increasing your melee-combat prowess or
if you QUALIFY for a different class, you can advance in that class...
let's say Wizard.

If you had selected to advance a level as a Wizard, you now would be
2nd level character, with one level as a Warrior and one level as a
Wizard.  That means you wouldn't have gained the melee-combat advance-
ment you would have gained as a Warrior, BUT you will gain some magic
casting abilities as a Wizard.

Some special notes is to bear in mind that some classes will enhance each
other better, in addition you have to QUALIFY to advance in the desired
class, finally there is a MAXIMUM-MULTICLASS value that is set by the
game that limits the number of classes you can take on.

See also:  MAXIMUM-MULTICLASS QUALIFY GAIN
