SAVING-THROWS FORTITUDE REFLEX WILLPOWER

Generally, when you are subject to an unusual or magical attack, you
get a saving throw to avoid or reduce the effect.  Similar to an
attack roll, a saving throw is a d20 roll plus a bonus based on
class, level and an ability score.  Your saving throw modifier is:
  Base save bonus + ability modifier

-Base Save Bonus
A saving throw modifier derived from character class and level.  Base
save bonuses increase at different rates for different character
classes.  Base save bonuses gained from different classes, such as
when characters are multiclass, will stack.

-Saving Throw Types
  Fortitude - this measures your ability to stand up to physical
punishment or attacks against your vitality or health.  Your
Constitution modifier applies to your fortitude saving throw.
  Reflex - These saves test your ability to dodge area attacks.  Your
dexterity modifies reflex saving throws.
  Will - These saves reflex your resistance to mental influence as
well as many magical effects.  Your wisdom modifier applies to this
save.

-Automatic Failures and Success
A natural 1 (the d20 comes up as 1) on a saving throw is always a
failure.  A natural 20 is always a success.

*Note:  This help entry is taken directly from:
http://www.d20srd.org/srd/combat/combatStatistics.htm

See also:  ATTACK-ROLL
